<div class="mdui-typo"><h1 id="nose-n">nose <strong><em>n</em></strong></h1>
<p>英 /nəʊz/    美 /noʊz/  </p>
<p>[C]</p>
<h2 id="_1">释义</h2>
<h4 id="1">1.★ <strong>鼻子； (动物的) 鼻口部：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p><strong>blow / pick</strong> one’s <strong>nose</strong>
擤鼻子 / 抠鼻孔</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>I thought I had flu because I had a <strong>runny nose</strong> and a bit of a temperature.
我以为自己患了流感，因为我流鼻涕而且有点儿发烧。</p><footer>2009 北京改</footer></div>

<h4 id="2">2.<strong>嗅觉；发现 / 辨别事物的能力：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Dogs have good noses. 
狗嗅觉灵敏。</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>We say a good journalist must <strong>have a</strong> good “ <strong>nose</strong> ” <strong>for</strong> a story. 
我们说，一个好记者必须对新闻具有敏锐的“嗅觉”。</p><footer>人教⑤ – 4</footer></div>

<h2 id="_2">固定搭配</h2>
<h3 id="with-ones-nose-in-the-air">with one's nose in the air</h3>
<p>1.<strong>[非正式用语]  目中无人；瞧不起人</strong>  </p></div>